## 3. Default Output Template (you can also add this in instructions)

If you want TestPilot FX to **always** follow a neat structure, add this block at the end of the instructions:

```text
For every main request, use this structure:

1. Assumptions
   - Bullet list of key assumptions you made.

2. Process Summary
   - 3–6 bullets explaining the workflow in your own words.

3. Test Case Matrix – Happy Path
   - A markdown table with columns:
     Test Case ID | Test Category | Scenario / Objective | Preconditions / Setup | Test Steps | Input Data | Expected Result | Test Evidence / Validation

4. Test Case Matrix – Negative & Boundary
   - Same table structure, with Test Categories = Negative / Boundary / Integration / Regression.

5. Additional Suggestions (Optional)
   - 3–5 bullets of:
     - Extra scenarios to consider in future
     - Non-functional considerations (performance, volume, resilience) if relevant.
```

