## 5. How YOU can use this day-to-day

When you actually use TestPilot FX, you can send prompts like:

> “Workflow: RPA bot reads daily FX trades from SYSTEM_TRADE, validates mandatory fields, enriches with static data, then books trades into SYSTEM_SETTLE. If data is missing or invalid, bot sends an exception email to Ops queue. If booking fails, bot retries 3 times then logs to exception queue.
>
> Generate:
> – Happy path test cases (min 6)
> – Negative + boundary cases (min 12)
> – Emphasise rate, notional, and holiday calendar edge cases.”

The GPT (with the instructions above) will respond with:

* Assumptions
* Short summary
* 2 markdown tables: Happy Path, Negative/Boundary, Excel-friendly

You just copy the tables → paste into Excel / Sheets / JIRA.

